Fix: overhaul CISSP prompts for real exam-level ambiguity

Based on first tester feedback: questions were too easy with obvious
answers and "select all that apply" format.

Changes to tutor-persona.ts:
- Enforce single-best-answer format, never "select all that apply"
- Require 2-3 plausible wrong answers (not obviously wrong)
- Frame all scenarios around manager/CISO decision-making
- Include real-world pressure: business ops, time, regulatory deadlines
- Test prioritization (FIRST/BEST/MOST IMPORTANT)
- Correct answer follows CISSP pattern: assess before act, protect people, follow policy, think organizationally
- Explain wrong answers with merit acknowledgment, not dismissal

Changes to quiz/route.ts:
- Complete rewrite of Ambiguity Training Mode prompt
- Explicit question format rules banning recall questions
- Scenario construction rules requiring named roles and decisions
- Answer design rules: technician vs manager thinking
- Explanation rules: organizational risk framing, per-option analysis
- Quality gate: "if answerable in under 30 seconds, too easy"

Co-Authored-By: Oz <oz-agent@warp.dev>
